<title>USA: Software Spectrum Q4 shr $0.02 vs $0.28.</title>
<headline>Software Spectrum Q4 shr $0.02 vs $0.28.</headline>
<dateline>GARLAND, Texas 1997-07-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Three months ended</p>
<p>		     April 30 1997	    March 31 1996</p>
<p> Shr		 $0.02		    $0.28</p>
<p> Net		 104			1,190</p>
<p> Revs		200,818		  99,605</p>
<p> Avg shrs	  4,366		    4,255</p>
<p>	 Year ended</p>
<p>		     April 30 1997	     March 31 1996</p>
<p> Shr	 loss  $0.20	   profit $1.73</p>
<p> Net	 loss  845	     profit 7,366</p>
<p> Revs		796,285		  398,501</p>
<p> Avg		 4,314		    4,260</p>
<p>(All data above 000s except per share numbers)</p>
<p>NOTE: Software centrum said the 1997 fiscal year included transition costs of $3.7 million relating to the aqcuisitions of Egghead Inc's CGE division and the Essentially Group.</p>
<p>It also said the 1997 quarter and year included $680,000 in goodwill and $2.67 million in amortization. The company added its Asia-Pacific operations posted an operating loss in the 1997 fiscal year.</p>
<p>Software changed its fiscal year-end to Arpil 30 from March 31. The company's full name is Software Spectrum Inc.</p>
